President Biden delivered a speech at Emory University in Atlanta, Georgia, addressing the recent mass shooting and rising hate crimes against Asian Americans. He expressed his condolences to the families of the victims and highlighted the need to stand together against hate and racism. The President emphasized the importance of combating xenophobia and hate crimes, and called on Congress to pass the COVID-19 Hate Crimes Act. He also urged Americans to continue following public health guidelines and get vaccinated to fight against the ongoing pandemic. Additionally, President Biden praised Georgia for its successful election and emphasized the importance of protecting the right to vote. He discussed the benefits of the American Rescue Plan, including financial support for families and investments in economic growth. The President concluded his speech by emphasizing the need for unity and collective action to address the challenges facing the nation.